"Enabling persistent signatures will allow signed requests without a timestamp. This means that the same link can be "
"used forever to access private information. This introduces the risk that if somebody finds out about the link, they "
"can access the same private information as yourself. By enabling this you agree to keep those links private and "
"ensure that no unauthorized people will use them."
msgstr ""

#: indico/modules/api/templates/_messages.html
msgid ""
"When disabling persistent signatures, all signed requests need a valid timestamp again. If you enable them again, old"
" persistent links will start working again - if you need to invalidate them, you have to create a new API key!"
msgstr ""

